  1: # Custom Neovim Kickstart Configuration
  2: 
  3: This is a personalized Neovim configuration based on [kickstart.nvim](https://github.com/nvim-lua/kickstart.nvim). It serves as a modular and understandable starting point, enhanced with specific tools for AI assistance, file management, and window handling.
  4: 
  5: ## Features
  6: 
  7: - **Package Manager**: [lazy.nvim](https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim)
  8: - **Colorscheme**: [tokyonight.nvim](https://github.com/folke/tokyonight.nvim) (Night variant)
  9: - **LSP**: Native LSP with [blink.cmp](https://github.com/saghen/blink.cmp) for autocompletion.
 10: - **Formatting**: [conform.nvim](https://github.com/stevearc/conform.nvim) for auto-formatting.
 11: - **Treesitter**: Syntax highlighting and parsing.
 12: - **Telescope**: Fuzzy finding.
 13: - **Symbol Navigation**: [aerial.nvim](https://github.com/stevearc/aerial.nvim) for code outline and structure.
 14: 
 15: ## Customizations
 16: 
 17: ### AI Integration
 18: 
 19: - **Plugin**: [codecompanion.nvim](https://github.com/olimorris/codecompanion.nvim)
 20: - **Default Adapter**: GitHub Copilot
 21: - **Available Adapters**: GitHub Copilot, Google Gemini, Claude Code
 22: - **Extensions**: Chat history (`codecompanion-history.nvim`) — open with `gh`, save with `gW` inside chat buffer.
 23: - **MCP Servers** (Model Context Protocol): External tool servers that extend the AI's capabilities via JSON-RPC over stdio. Toggle with `/mcp` in a chat buffer.
 24:   - **Context7** (`@upstash/context7-mcp`): Live, up-to-date library/framework documentation. No API key.
 25:   - **Sequential Thinking** (`@modelcontextprotocol/server-sequential-thinking`): Structured step-by-step reasoning with revision/branching. No API key.
 26:   - **PDF Reader** (`pdf-reader-mcp`): Extracts text and metadata from PDF files. No API key.
 27: - **MCP Auto-start**: Only Context7 starts automatically. Sequential Thinking, PDF Reader, and Memory are on-demand — toggle with `/mcp` in chat.
 28: - **Prompt Library**: Switchable AI profiles loaded from external files (`~/.local/share/nvim/prompts/`). Available via `<leader>aa`:
 29:   - **Sofi** (`sofi`) — Philosophy mentor (Práxis Filosófica)
 30:   - **Study** (`iam-study`) — OAuth2, OIDC, Federation tutor
 31:   - **Architect** (`iam-arch`) — IAM architecture & design advisor
 32:   - `Browse Chat History` (`history`) and `Browse Summaries` (`summaries`)
 33: - **Statusline Spinner**: A braille spinner animates in the statusline while a request is in flight; `fidget.nvim` shows toast notifications on start/done.
 34: - **Keymaps**:
 35:   - `<leader>ac`: Toggle AI Chat
 36:   - `<leader>ai`: AI Inline Edit (Visual mode)
 37:   - `<leader>aa`: AI Actions
 38:   - `<leader>as`: Open Sofi (Philosophy Mentor) chat
 39:   - `gzs` _(chat buffer)_: Create chat summary
 40:   - `gzb` _(chat buffer)_: Browse saved summaries
 41: - **Custom Commands**:
 42:   - `:CCTitle <new title>`: Rename the current chat (updates UI, history, and buffer name)
 43: 
 44: ### Inline AI Suggestions
 45: 
 46: - **Plugin**: [copilot.lua](https://github.com/zbirenbaum/copilot.lua)
 47: - **Description**: Inline code suggestions powered by GitHub Copilot, auto-triggered on insert mode.
 48: - **Keymaps**:
 49:   - `<C-l>`: Accept suggestion
 50:   - `<M-]>` / `<M-[>`: Next / Previous suggestion
 51:   - `<C-]>`: Dismiss suggestion
 52: 
 53: ### Code Outline & Symbol Navigation
 54: 
 55: - **Plugin**: [aerial.nvim](https://github.com/stevearc/aerial.nvim)
 56: - **Description**: Displays code structure (functions, classes, methods, variables) in a tree view for navigation and understanding code organization.
 57: - **Keymaps**:
 58:   - `<leader>ts`: Toggle symbols sidebar
 59:   - `<leader>tS`: Toggle symbols for all buffers
 60:   - Inside aerial: `Enter` to jump, `q` to close, `j/k` to navigate, `{/}` to jump between symbols
 61: 
 62: ### File Management
 63: 
 64: - **Plugin**: [oil.nvim](https://github.com/stevearc/oil.nvim)
 65: - **Description**: Edit your filesystem like a normal buffer.
 66: - **Keymaps**:
 67:   - `-`: Open parent directory
 68:   - `<C-x>`: Open in horizontal split
 69:   - `<C-v>`: Open in vertical split
 70:   - `<C-t>`: Open in new tab
 71: 
 72: ### Window Management
 73: 
 74: - **Plugin**: [vim-maximizer](https://github.com/szw/vim-maximizer)
 75: - **Keymaps**:
 76:   - `<leader>ww`: Toggle maximize current window
 77: 
 78: ### Markdown
 79: 
 80: - **Plugins**:
 81:   - [render-markdown.nvim](https://github.com/MeanderingProgrammer/render-markdown.nvim) — Rich rendering inside Neovim (also renders CodeCompanion chat buffers).
 82:   - [markdown-preview.nvim](https://github.com/iamcco/markdown-preview.nvim) — Live preview in browser with Mermaid diagram support.
 83: - **Keymaps**:
 84:   - `<leader>mr`: Toggle Markdown render (in-editor)
 85:   - `<leader>mp`: Toggle Markdown preview (browser)
 86: 
 87: ## Core Keymaps
 88: 
 89: | Key           | Description                             |
 90: | ------------- | --------------------------------------- |
 91: | `<Space>`     | Leader Key                              |
 92: | `<Esc>`       | Clear search highlights                 |
 93: | `<C-h/j/k/l>` | Navigate between windows                |
 94: | `<leader>sh`  | Search Help                             |
 95: | `<leader>sk`  | Search Keymaps                          |
 96: | `<leader>sf`  | Search Files                            |
 97: | `<leader>sg`  | Live Grep                               |
 98: | `<leader>f`   | Format buffer                           |
 99: | `<leader>ts`  | Toggle code outline (symbols sidebar)   |
100: | `<leader>tS`  | Toggle code outline for all buffers     |
101: | `<leader>as`  | Open Sofi (Philosophy Mentor)           |
102: | `<leader>q`   | Open diagnostic Quickfix list           |
103: | `<C-l>`       | Accept Copilot suggestion (Insert mode) |
104: | `<leader>mr`  | Toggle Markdown render (in-editor)      |
105: | `<leader>mp`  | Toggle Markdown preview (browser)       |
106: 
107: ## Language Support
108: 
109: Out of the box support (LSP, Formatting, Highlighting) for:
110: 
111: - **Lua**: `lua_ls`, `stylua`
112: - **Python**: `pyright`, `ruff`
113: - **Go**: `gopls` (with built-in staticcheck), `goimports`, `gofumpt`
114: - **Ruby**: `ruby-lsp`, `rubocop`
115: - **JavaScript/TypeScript**: `ts_ls`, `eslint-lsp`, `prettierd`
116: - **CSS/HTML**: `prettierd`
117: - **Markdown**: `marksman`, `prettierd`, `markdownlint`
118: - **YAML/JSON**: `yaml-language-server`, `prettierd`
119: 
120: ## Installation
121: 
122: ### Prerequisites
123: 
124: - Neovim >= 0.10.0
125: - Git
126: - Make, GCC (for Telescope fzf-native)
127: - Ripgrep, fd (for Telescope)
128: - Nerd Font (recommended)
129: - Node.js >= 18 (for JS/TS LSP and formatters — recommended via [nvm](https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm))
130: - Ruby >= 3.0 (for Ruby LSP — recommended via [rbenv](https://github.com/rbenv/rbenv))
131: 
132: ### Setup
133: 
134: 1. Backup your existing configuration:
135: 
136:    ```sh
137:    mv ~/.config/nvim ~/.config/nvim.bak
138:    mv ~/.local/share/nvim ~/.local/share/nvim.bak
139:    ```
140: 
141: 2. Clone this repository:
142: 
143:    ```sh
144:    git clone <your-repo-url> ~/.config/nvim
145:    ```
146: 
147: 3. Start Neovim:
148:    ```sh
149:    nvim
150:    ```
151:    `lazy.nvim` will automatically install all plugins.
152: 
153: ## Structure
154: 
155: - `init.lua`: Main configuration file.
156: - `lua/custom/plugins/`: User-added plugins (CodeCompanion, Copilot, Markdown, Oil, Maximizer, Aerial, etc.).
157: - `lua/kickstart/plugins/`: Core Kickstart plugins (Debug, Lint, Gitsigns, etc.).
